com.googlecode.swtfinder.core.finder
Class Finder

java.lang.Object
  com.googlecode.swtfinder.core.finder.Finder

public abstract class Finder
extends java.lang.Object

This class is used to find a Control in View/Editor or under any Control
all method of this class can be called both in UI thread and non ui thread.

Author:
Ben.Xu (xufengbing@gmail.com)

findIndexByClassInEclipseView

public org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Control findIndexByClassInEclipseView(java.lang.String viewID,
                                                                     java.lang.Class clazz,
                                                                     int index)
this method is used to locate a special Control in an eclipse view with viewID
this method will always try to check if the current active part is the view with viewID,
if it is, it will find the control in this view.
the condition used to find the control is ConditionClassAssignableFind

Parameters:
viewID - view's id
clazz - find condition
index - start from 1
Returns:
the control found
